215: // NewReflectorWithOptions creates a new Reflector object which will keep the
216: // given store up to date with the server's contents for the given
217: // resource. Reflector promises to only put things in the store that
218: // have the type of expectedType, unless expectedType is nil. If
219: // resyncPeriod is non-zero, then the reflector will periodically
220: // consult its ShouldResync function to determine whether to invoke
221: // the Store's Resync operation; `ShouldResync==nil` means always
222: // "yes".  This enables you to use reflectors to periodically process
223: // everything as well as incrementally processing the things that
